==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uttermost
<hw>Ut"ter*most</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Utter</er>, <pos>a.</pos>; cf. <er>Utmost</er>, and
<er>Outermost</er>.]</ety> <def>Extreme; utmost; being; in the farthest,
greatest, or highest degree; <as>as, the <ex>uttermost</ex> extent or
end</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In this <xex>uttermost</xex> distress.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1590 pr=PI -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uttermost</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uttermost
<hw>Ut"ter*most`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The utmost; the
highest or greatest degree; the farthest extent.</def>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherefore he is able also to save them to the <qex>uttermost</qex>
that come unto God by him.</q> <rj><qau>Heb. vii. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He cannot have sufficient honor done unto him; but the
<qex>uttermost</qex> we can do, we must.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utterness</ent>⟦br⟧
